    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Money in the form of bars of metal. Examples include stamped copper bars issued 1796-1818 for use as money in the Dutch East Indies, and various African examples of metal masses, spheres, or flat regular plates used as money.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
